Pattern Recognition
📌 Tree + Recursion + Mirror Comparison

Key Observation:
A symmetric tree is simply a tree whose left subtree
is the mirror image of its right subtree.
Instead of checking levels or traversals explicitly:
Compare two nodes at a time.

Mirror Rule:
left->left  ↔ right->right
left->right ↔ right->left
This naturally leads to a recursive solution.

Interview Insight
Many candidates immediately think of:
Level Order Traversal (BFS)
But the cleanest solution is:
Recursive Mirror Check because symmetry is inherently a recursive property.
